  "summary": "Following a scream from Harumi, the narrator and Mutsuji rush to the second-floor corridor. There, they encounter the servant Shima, who is stumbling and incoherent while attempting to report that something has happened to Aoyama. The narrator also finds the housekeeper, Yamauchi, slumped against a door in a state of terror. Looking where she is staring, the narrator discovers a white head placed on a box, which appears to be floating against a dim wall.\n\nMukutokun observes that the murderer has taken advantage of the group, suggesting that Arai is likely being used as a decoy rather than being the killer. Jirogawa notes a pattern in the crimes: the killer frequently leaves body parts missing, such as a head or a body. Although the head was found in a room with very little blood, Detective Horikoshi’s team finds no clues in the closets, suggesting the decapitation occurred elsewhere.\n\nAt 12:20, Detective Nakamura reports finding a body in a first-floor storage room used for food storage. The room, kept at 4-5 degrees Celsius, is a bloody crime scene where the headless body of Akibabe lies in an \"X\" shape on the white floor. A maid named Miyuki discovered the body while preparing lunch. Mutsuji suggests the killer may have timed the discovery to create a dramatic effect, potentially intending for the body or the head to be found first to manipulate the investigation. The group concludes that the victim likely died from a beating before being decapitated.",
